      <title id="i2127092"
             outputclass="H302"
             xtrf="Grey"
             class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">517.202</ph> Use of options.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d332e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li audience="GSAR"
                otherprops="abc"
                xtrf="Grey"
                class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d329e17" outputclass="H5_abcRunIn" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                     Options
may be used when they meet one or more of the following objectives:</p>
               <ol id="d332e36" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li audience="GSAR"
                      otherprops="123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d329e40" xtrf="Grey" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                          Reduce
procurement lead time and associated costs.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li audience="GSAR"
                      otherprops="123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d329e49" xtrf="Grey" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                          Ensure
continuity of contract support.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li audience="GSAR"
                      otherprops="123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d329e58" xtrf="Grey" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                          Improve
overall contractor performance.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li audience="GSAR"
                      otherprops="123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d329e67" xtrf="Grey" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                          Facilitate
longer term contractual relationships with those contractors that
continually meet or exceed quality performance expectations.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li audience="GSAR"
                otherprops="abc"
                outputclass="Grey_H5_abc"
                xtrf="Grey"
                class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d329e78"
                  outputclass="H5_abc"
                  xtrf="Grey"
                  class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                    An
option is normally in the Government’s interest in the following
circumstances:</p>
               <ol id="d332e84" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li audience="GSAR"
                      otherprops="123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d329e88" xtrf="Grey" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                          There
is an anticipated need for additional supplies or services during
the contract term.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li audience="GSAR"
                      otherprops="123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d329e97" xtrf="Grey" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                          When
there is both a need for additional supplies or services beyond
the basic contract period and the use of multi-year contracting
authority is inappropriate.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li audience="GSAR"
                      otherprops="123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d329e106" xtrf="Grey" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                          There
is a need for continuity of supply or service support.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li audience="GSAR"
                otherprops="abc"
                outputclass="Grey_H5_abc"
                xtrf="Grey"
                class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d329e117"
                  outputclass="H6_123"
                  xtrf="Grey"
                  class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                    An
option shall not be used if the market price is likely to change
substantially and an economic price adjustment clause inadequately
protects the Government's interest.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
